text.tspan: Gap in GDP per hour worked with respect to the United States
Figure illustrates the gap in GDP per hour worked with respect to the United States. The gap is calculated by taking a
country's GDP per hour worked minus that of the US, divided by US GDP per hour worked. A positive gap suggests
the country is more productive (has higher GDP per hour worked) than the US.
Source: OECD - Productivity - Level of GDP per capita and productivity
